President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Haywood Stirling Gilliam, Jr. to serve on the United States District Court for the Northern District of California. Gilliam is currently a partner at Covington & Burling LLP, where he serves as Vice-Chair of the firm's White Collar Defense and Investigations practice group. He has previously worked at Bingham McCutchen LLP and served as an Assistant United States Attorney in the Northern District of California. Gilliam has also worked at McCutchen, Doyle, Brown & Enersen and served as a law clerk to Judge Thelton E. Henderson. He obtained his J.D. from Stanford Law School and his B.A. magna cum laude from Yale University. President Obama expressed confidence that Gilliam will serve with integrity and a steadfast commitment to justice.